Final assessment

The blueprint you've created is ambitious enough to guide product evolution for many years. The limiting factor from here is not architecture—it's disciplined execution, customer validation, and building a team capable of delivering enterprise-grade software.

The strongest path is to treat this blueprint as a long-term north star, while focusing your first product on solving one painful, high-value problem exceptionally well. That creates the customer base, revenue, and engineering maturity needed to grow toward the broader vision over time